##CCENT016 - Understanding VLANs and Trunks

#Vlans
	-Logically Groups Users
	-Segments Broadcast Domains
	-Subnet Correlation
	-Access Control
	-Quality of Service

*Useful for segmenting network traffic and users. 
-Example Vlan Setup
	-VLAN10 192.168.1.0/24
	-VLAN20 192.168.2.0/24


#Trunks
	-Carries all VLANS
	-Should be faster than other ports if possible
	-CISCO - TRUNK PORT / OTHERS - TAGGED PORT
	-TRUNK/TAGGED Ports put the vlan number tags on each packet which is stripped off at the next switch
